[SN]TITLE[SN]
Police appeal as two hurt in Dundee motorcycle crash

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Police have appealed for witnesses after two motorcyclists were injured in a crash in Dundee.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The two bikes collided on Dayton Drive at about 17:00 on Monday, with both riders requiring medical treatment.
One of them, a 24-year-old man, continues to be treated at Ninewells Hospital for serious injuries to his head and body.
Police are investigating the full circumstances of the crash, and appealed for witnesses to come forward.
Dayton Drive is part of Dundee's Camperdown Leisure Park. Officers thanked members of the public who helped attend to the two men following the crash.
